<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Count3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Count,</orth> vb., 1) to number, to reckon: <cit><quote>c. the clock,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 12.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 12, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to c. atomies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.245" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 245</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. thy way with sighs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 89</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 142</bibl>. <cit><quote>to c. o'er,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 172</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to account, to esteem, to think: <cit><quote>--ing best to be with you alone,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 75.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 75, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing no old thing old,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.108.7" default="NO" valid="yes">108, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.121.8" default="NO" valid="yes">121, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.127.1" default="NO" valid="yes">127, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.141.13" default="NO" valid="yes">141, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.263" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.263" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 263</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 3, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.245" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 245</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.261" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 261</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 15</bibl>.
<lb />3) Followed by <emph>of,</emph> == to attend to, to take notice of: <cit><quote>no man --s of her beauty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 1, 65</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. of this, the count's a fool,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.258" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 258</bibl></cit>.
<lb />Transitively in the same sense? <cit><quote>I'll c. his favours,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 78</bibl></cit> (M. Edd. <emph>court</emph>). cf. <cit><quote>nor mother, wife, nor England's -- ed queen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 47</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>